include ../layout

+layout
    h1 Badges
    p.intro-text
        | Documentation and examples for badges, our small count and labeling component.
    h2 Example
    p.intro-text
        | Badges scale to match the size of the immediate parent element by using relative font sizing and 
        code(style='color:red') em 
        | units.
    .stack
        .stack__item.row
            .col-6
                .sat-card.sat-card_md
                    h1
                        | Example heading 
                        span.badge.badge-secondary New
                    h2
                        | Example heading 
                        span.badge.badge-secondary New
                    h3
                        | Example heading 
                        span.badge.badge-secondary New
                    h4
                        | Example heading 
                        span.badge.badge-secondary New
                    h5
                        | Example heading 
                        span.badge.badge-secondary New
                    h6
                        | Example heading 
                        span.badge.badge-secondary New
    pre
        code.html
            |&lt;h1&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge badge-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
            |&lt;h2&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge badge-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
            |&lt;h3&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge badge-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
            |&lt;h4&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge badge-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
            |&lt;h5&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge badge-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
            |&lt;h6&gt;Example heading &lt;span class="badge badge-secondary"&gt;New&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h6&gt;
    p.intro-text
        | Badges can be used as part of links or buttons to provide a counter.
    .stack
        .stack__item.row
            .col-6
                .sat-card.sat-card_md
                    button.btn.btn-primary(type='button')
                        | Notifications 
                        span.badge.badge-light 4
    pre
        code.html
            |&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;
            |   Notifications &lt;span class="badge badge-light"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;
            |&lt;/button&gt;
    p.intro-text
        | Note that depending on how they are used, badges may be confusing for users of screen readers and similar assistive technologies. While the styling of badges provides a visual cue as to their purpose, these users will simply be presented with the content of the badge. Depending on the specific situation, these badges may seem like random additional words or numbers at the end of a sentence, link, or button.
    p.intro-text
        | Unless the context is clear (as with the “Notifications” example, where it is understood that the “4” is the number of notifications), consider including additional context with a visually hidden piece of additional text.
    .stack
        .stack__item.row
            .col-6
                .sat-card.sat-card_md
                    button.btn.btn-primary(type='button')
                        | Profile 
                        span.badge.badge-light 9
                        span.sr-only unread messages
    pre
        code.html
            |&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;
            |    Profile &lt;span class="badge badge-light"&gt;9&lt;/span&gt;
            |    &lt;span class="sr-only"&gt;unread messages&lt;/span&gt;
            |&lt;/button&gt;
    h2 Contextual variations
    p.intro-text
        | Add any of the below mentioned modifier classes to change the appearance of a badge.
    .stack
        .stack__item.row
            .col-6
                .sat-card.sat-card_md
                    span.badge.badge-primary Primary
                    span.badge.badge-secondary Secondary
                    span.badge.badge-success Success
                    span.badge.badge-danger Danger
                    span.badge.badge-warning Warning
                    span.badge.badge-info Info
                    span.badge.badge-light Light
                    span.badge.badge-dark Dark
    h5 Conveying meaning to assistive technologies
    p.intro-text
        | Using color to add meaning only provides a visual indication, which will not be conveyed to users of assistive technologies – such as screen readers. Ensure that information denoted by the color is either obvious from the content itself (e.g. the visible text), or is included through alternative means, such as additional text hidden with the 
        code(style='color:red') .sr-only 
        | class.
    h2 Pill badges
    p.intro-text
        | Use the 
        code(style='color:red') .badge-pill 
        | modifier class to make badges more rounded (with a larger 
        code(style='color:red') border-radius 
        | and additional horizontal 
        code(style='color:red') padding
        | ). Useful if you miss the badges from v3.
    .stack
        .stack__item.row
            .col-6
                .sat-card.sat-card_md
                    span.badge.badge-pill.badge-primary Primary
                    span.badge.badge-pill.badge-secondary Secondary
                    span.badge.badge-pill.badge-success Success
                    span.badge.badge-pill.badge-danger Danger
                    span.badge.badge-pill.badge-warning Warning
                    span.badge.badge-pill.badge-info Info
                    span.badge.badge-pill.badge-light Light
                    span.badge.badge-pill.badge-dark Dark
    pre
        code.html
            |&lt;span class="badge badge-pill badge-primary"&gt;Primary&lt;/span&gt;
            |&lt;span class="badge badge-pill badge-secondary"&gt;Secondary&lt;/span&gt;
            |&lt;span class="badge badge-pill badge-success"&gt;Success&lt;/span&gt;
            |&lt;span class="badge badge-pill badge-danger"&gt;Danger&lt;/span&gt;
            |&lt;span class="badge badge-pill badge-warning"&gt;Warning&lt;/span&gt;
            |&lt;span class="badge badge-pill badge-info"&gt;Info&lt;/span&gt;
            |&lt;span class="badge badge-pill badge-light"&gt;Light&lt;/span&gt;
            |&lt;span class="badge badge-pill badge-dark"&gt;Dark&lt;/span&gt;
    h2 Links
    p.intro-text
        | Using the contextual 
        code(style='color:red') .badge-* 
        | classes on an 
        code(style='color:red') &lt;a&gt; 
        | element quickly provide actionable badges with hover and focus states.
    .stack
        .stack__item.row
            .col-6
                .sat-card.sat-card_md
                    a.badge.badge-primary(href='#') Primary
                    a.badge.badge-secondary(href='#') Secondary
                    a.badge.badge-success(href='#') Success
                    a.badge.badge-danger(href='#') Danger
                    a.badge.badge-warning(href='#') Warning
                    a.badge.badge-info(href='#') Info
                    a.badge.badge-light(href='#') Light
                    a.badge.badge-dark(href='#') Dark
    pre
        code.html
            |&lt;a href="#" class="badge badge-primary"&gt;Primary&lt;/a&gt;
            |&lt;a href="#" class="badge badge-secondary"&gt;Secondary&lt;/a&gt;
            |&lt;a href="#" class="badge badge-success"&gt;Success&lt;/a&gt;
            |&lt;a href="#" class="badge badge-danger"&gt;Danger&lt;/a&gt;
            |&lt;a href="#" class="badge badge-warning"&gt;Warning&lt;/a&gt;
            |&lt;a href="#" class="badge badge-info"&gt;Info&lt;/a&gt;
            |&lt;a href="#" class="badge badge-light"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt;
            |&lt;a href="#" class="badge badge-dark"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt;


